31 SECTION 2.1.(a) G.S. 135-18.10A(c) reads as rewritten:
32 "(c) If a member or former member whose benefits under the Retirement System were
33 forfeited under this section, except for the return of member contributions plus interest,
34 subsequently receives an unconditional pardon of innocence, or the conviction is vacated or set
35 aside for any reason, then the member or former member may seek a reversal of the benefit
36 forfeiture by presenting sufficient evidence to the State Treasurer. Board of Trustees. If the State
37 Treasurer Board of Trustees determines a reversal of the benefit forfeiture is appropriate, then all
38 benefits will be restored upon repayment of all accumulated contributions plus interest.
39 Repayment of all accumulated contributions that have been received by the individual under the
40 forfeiture provisions of this section must be made in a total lump-sum payment with interest
41 compounded annually at a rate of six and one-half percent (6.5%) for each calendar year from
42 the year of forfeiture to the year of repayment. An individual receiving a reversal of benefit
43 forfeiture must receive reinstatement of the service credit forfeited."
