10 SECTION 7.6.(b) G.S. 128-29(g)(2) reads as rewritten:
11 "(g) Legislative Enactment Implementation Arrangement. – The Legislative Enactment
12 Implementation Arrangement, or LEIA, is established effective October 1, 2017, and placed
13 under the management of the Board of Trustees. The purpose of the LEIA is to provide for timely
14 administrative implementation of legislative provisions regarding the retirement of, or payment
15 of retirement benefits to, public officers or public employees. The LEIA shall have the following
16 parameters:
17 …
18 (2) Funding of the LEIA. – In the event that that (i) the General Assembly creates
19 or modifies any provision for the retirement of, or payment of retirement
20 benefits to, public officers or public employees that has a cost savings as
21 measured by actuarial note required by Article 15 of Chapter 120 of the
22 General Statutes, or (ii) the Board of Trustees identifies a specific
23 administrative or information technology purpose that is necessary to prevent
24 an interruption to the normal operation of the Retirement System, the Board
25 of Trustees may direct up to one hundredth percent (0.01%) of the required
26 contributions to fund the LEIA. These funds must be deposited in a separate
27 fund from the fund into which regular employer contributions are deposited
28 for the Retirement System. The Board of Trustees shall not direct any
29 employer contributions into the LEIA after January 1, 2035."
30 SECTION 7.7. G.S. 135-48.54(b)(2) reads as rewritten:
31 "(b) The board of directors of a charter school operated by a private nonprofit corporation
32 or a charter school operated by a municipality may elect to become a participating employer in
33 the Plan. The following shall apply to that election:
34 …
35 (2) If the election is made at any time after two years from the date that both
36 parties have signed the written charter under G.S. 115C-218.15, then the board
37 of directors of that charter school shall file an application with the Board of
38 Trustees for participation in the Plan on a form approved by the Board of
39 Trustees. The application shall be subject to approval by the Board of Trustees
40 and notification of approval or denial of the application shall be provided by
41 the Board of Trustees to the board of directors within 180 days of receipt of
42 the complete application. Upon approval of the application by the Board of
43 Trustees, the charter school shall become a participating employing unit in the
44 Plan. The board of directors shall provide written notification of the election,
45 the submission of the application required under this subdivision, and the
46 approval of that application by the Board of Trustees to the Charter Schools
47 Review Board and the State Board of Education. This written notification
48 shall include the date that the charter school employees shall be enrolled in
49 the Plan. For any charter school employee hired after the initial enrollment
50 date, this election is effective as of the date of that employee's entry into
51 eligible service. The Board of Trustees may (i) delegate its powers and duties
